^-|ht|e|qx|BRD, beginning|CS||CP||fp||at|^b@2In this section we are going to be on the receiving side. Partner opens a suit and the RHO doubles. Without RHO putting his nose in our tent we could have been in a cushy constructive bidding. But now we are in competitive bidding where things are greatly different. 

Howard Schutzman covers this issue in his March and April 2012 lesson series in BIL - "Bidding over Opponent's Takeout Doubles." The lessons are converted to a BBO movie - "Raises In Competition" - which you can find either in BIL library at |CP|1|AT|^*Hwww.bilbridge.com^*N|CP||AT| or in Howard's web site at |CP|1|AT|^*Hwww.bridgesights.com/hondobridge/^*N|CP||AT|. The link to the BBO movie is |CP|1|AT|^*Hhttp://www.bridgesights.com/hondobridge/hondoviewer/hondoviewer.php?sf=raisesincompetition^*N|CP||AT|.

In synopsis, a condensed version of Howard's lessons will be presented in three following sections. Please click one of the blue links below to start that section. You can return to this page afterward. Or just click the forward arrow and begin the synopsis from the start. 
