qx|RD1,Bidding Over 1 of a Major after a Takeout Double|cs|1|fp|2|cp|4|at|
^-{    Bidding Over 1 of a Major after a Takeout Double    }
^-|CP||FP||CS||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*BHoward: ^*N|cp||at|One important point I like to emphasize first is that a new bid by responder, after opponent's double, shows less than 10 points. For example 1@H-x-2@C is less than 10 points - keep that in mind. |
PG| ***** 1 ***** |


AT|

Some people play something slightly more complicated, which I do not particularly care for. All one level bids over the double are forcing and can be made with 10+ points, but 2 level bids are not. I find that very counter-intuitive and confusing. Using that system 1@D-x-1@S can be and often is stronger than  1@D-x-2@C.|
PG| ***** 2 ***** |


AT| 

The second important note is the 1@H/1@S-double-1N. In this auction 1NT promises 8-11.|
PG| ***** 3 ***** |


AT|

The third important note is that Bergen Raises are off after competition (unless you agree otherwise). I will discuss this topic later.|
PG| ***** 4 ***** |


AT| For ease of explanation let us divide the responder's hand (your hand in quizzes) in two categories:|
PG| ***** 5 ***** |


hT|m|AT|^CA. Hands with 6-9 points.|
PG| ***** 6 ***** |


hT|m|AT|^CA. Hands with 6-9 points.
^cB. Hands with 10+ points.|
PG| ***** 7 ***** |


at|

In category A - with 6-9 and support for partner's suit you bid based on the Law of Total tricks.|
PG| ***** 8 ***** |


AT|
Bid 2 with 3-card support (just like after an overcall).|
PG| ***** 9 ***** |


AT|
Bid 3 with 4-card support and less than a limit raise. In competition you want to play weak jump raises. Remember the Law of Total Tricks is your friend :).|
PG| ***** 10 ***** |


AT|
Bid 4 with 5-card support.|
PG| ***** 11 ***** |


AT|

In category B - with 10+ points you redouble with 3-card support.|
PG| ***** 12 ***** |


AT|
You should bid 2NT (Jordan 2NT) with 4-card support and limit raise or better.|
PG| ***** 13 ***** |


AT|

Some experts recommend bidding redouble with 10 points holding less than 3-card support and bid 2NT with 3+ card support and limit raise or better. |
PG| ***** 14 ***** |


AT|

Let us look at some examples for 1 of a major followed by takeout double. Bergen Raises are off (unless you agree otherwise).|
PG| ***** 15 ***** |


