qx|RD2,Bergen Raises after a Take Out Double|cs|1|fp|2|cp|4|at|
^-{    Bergen Raises after a Take Out Double    }
^-|CP||FP||CS||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*BHoward: ^*N|cp||at|Many experts play Bergen Raises are off after competition. But I think you can and should play they are on, although that is not standard. Therefore, if you play Reverse Bergen Raises 3@C is 10+ 4-card support, and 3@D is 7-9 with 4 card support. I recommend you play Jordan 2N is a 3-card raise (since 3@C is a 4-card raise). All these bids are now alertable. Next there are a few examples.|
PG| ***** 38 ***** |


NT||
