QX|RD3,Bidding Over 1 of a Minor after a Takeout Double|cs|1|fp|2|cp|4|at|
^-{    Bidding Over 1 of a Minor after a Takeout Double    }
^-|CP||FP||CS||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*BHoward: ^*N|cp||at|The responses after minor suit openings are basically similar to what you do after an overcall. First a few important points to remember.|
PG| ***** 56 ***** |


AT|

Inverted Minor Raises are off.|
PG| ***** 57 ***** |


AT|

If you have a nice major bid it. But remember the doubler tends to promise the major, so don't bid a weak suit. You only need 4 cards, but you should have at least a couple of honors. And of course the redouble rule applies, so if you bid 1 of a major you have less than 10 points.|
PG| ***** 58 ***** |


AT|

Here again redouble is the only way to show 10 points. You bid 1N with 8-11 points and you should bid 2N with five card support and 10+ points. Weak jump shifts and weak raises are highly recommended. We can get a better understanding of the bidding with the following examples.|
PG| ***** 59 ***** |


